**Business Plan: Tiki Tykes Island Play– Amelia Island, Florida**

---

Executive Summary

Tiki Tykes Island Play is a unique, community-centered destination where parents can bring their young children to explore, play, and grow all within a safe, engaging, and thoughtfully designed environment. More than just a play space, Tiki Tykes aims to fill a much-needed gap on Amelia Island by fostering meaningful connections among local families.

Our vision is to create a welcoming, high-end hub where parents of young children can feel seen, supported, and inspired. Whether it's making new friends, sharing parenting experiences, or simply enjoying quality time with their children, families will find Tiki Tykes to be a vibrant space that nurtures both child development and adult connection. We are committed to cultivating an inclusive, uplifting atmosphere that becomes a foundational part of daily life for young families across the community.

**Highlights:**

• Immersive, Custom-Designed Play Environment \- Tiki Tykes Island Play will feature a state-of-the-art soft play area, developed by an industry-leading designer. The space will include a one-of-a-kind “All About Amelia Island” cityscape, bringing the beauty and wonder of the local coastline indoors. This climate-controlled environment is designed to captivate young minds and bodies — an ideal offering in a region known for both hot summers and cooler winter months.

• Membership-Driven Revenue Model \- By prioritizing package passes and recurring memberships, Tiki Tykes Island Play will establish consistent monthly cash flow while building long-term customer relationships. This model encourages frequent visits and supports sustainable growth from the start.

• Community-Driven Business Partnerships \- Strategic partnerships with local businesses from coffee and snacks to branded merchandise will enrich the customer experience and reinforce Tiki Tykes as a true community hub. These collaborations will also help foster support from both residents and neighboring small businesses.

• Commitment to Customer Feedback \- Frequent focus groups and direct engagement with families will be central to our operations. This ongoing dialogue ensures our offerings remain responsive, relevant, and closely aligned with the evolving needs of both children and parents in the area.

 

• Strategic Location in a Growing Market \- Amelia Island is experiencing steady population growth, especially among young families. Tiki Tykes carefully chosen location is designed to meet the rising demand for child-centered, community-focused experiences in this expanding market.

**Goals and Objectives:**

Our overarching goal is to become a trusted cornerstone of the parenting community on Amelia Island — a vibrant, welcoming hub where families with young children come not only to play, but to connect, share, and thrive. We aim to build a dynamic and inclusive environment that continuously evolves to meet the needs of local parents and their children. Through active engagement, collaborative partnerships, and a deep-rooted presence in the community, we will cultivate a loyal and inspired network of families.

 **Key Objectives:**

·       Establish a Core Parent Advisory Group (“Tiki Testers”) \- Build lasting relationships with 5–8 families from diverse backgrounds within the Amelia Island area. These families will act as our trusted advisory group, providing ongoing feedback and suggestions to shape the Tiki Tykes experience. In appreciation for their time and insights, they will receive exclusive perks such as complimentary play passes, early access to new features, and branded merchandise.

·       Host Ongoing Parent Focus Groups \- Conduct regularly scheduled focus groups with a rotating selection of parents to ensure a wide range of voices are heard. These sessions will keep us in tune with the community’s evolving needs and allow us to adapt and improve continuously based on real-time insights.

·       Foster Strategic Community Partnerships \- Collaborate with local businesses, wellness professionals, and service providers throughout Northeast Florida. By curating a network of trusted partners, we will transform Tiki Tykes into a one-stop family hub that delivers value well beyond play — offering resources, products, and support that enrich the parenting journey.

·       Engage Actively in Community Life \- Maintain a visible and genuine presence throughout the Amelia Island community. This includes volunteering with local organizations, participating in parenting groups, and showing up at family-centered events. Our goal is to be recognized not only as a local business, but as a dedicated community partner and advocate for families.

**Mission Statement**

At Tiki Tykes Island Play, our mission is to spark imagination, connection, and joyful play through immersive, beach-inspired experiences that celebrate the unique spirit of Amelia Island.

We are dedicated to creating a safe, enriching environment where young children can explore, imagine, and thrive. Rooted in the charm and history of our coastal home, our thoughtfully designed play structures and island-themed settings encourage creativity, inspire wonder, and foster meaningful family connections. Through warm, community-centered experiences, we aim to build lasting memories and a sense of belonging for families of young children.

**Keys to Success**

• Ongoing Community Engagement \- Remain deeply connected to the evolving needs and preferences of local families by actively collecting feedback through surveys, focus groups, and casual conversations. Regularly incorporate this input to refine offerings and ensure continued relevance and resonance within the Amelia Island community.

• Effective Social Media Presence \- Leverage engaging and consistent social media campaigns to build brand awareness, foster a sense of community, and cultivate a loyal local following. A strong digital presence will be essential for both outreach and retention.

• Customer Retention Through Memberships \- Prioritize recurring revenue through attractive monthly and annual membership options. This focus will not only ensure financial stability but also help develop a strong base of returning customers who feel invested in the Tiki Tykes experience.

• High-Quality, Thematic Design \- Maintain a polished, cohesive design throughout the play space that reflects the charm of Amelia Island. By blending visual appeal with functionality, we will create a high-end experience that feels both immersive and welcoming for families.

**Description of Business**

Tiki Tykes Island Play is an indoor, beach-themed play space located in the heart of Amelia Island, Florida, designed specifically for families with infants, toddlers, and young children. Our mission is to provide a safe, stimulating, and community-driven environment where children can play and explore while parents relax, connect, and build lasting relationships.

Inspired by the natural beauty and rich coastal heritage of Amelia Island, Tiki Tykes offers an immersive play experience through thoughtfully designed soft play structures, imaginative coastal elements, and interactive features that support early childhood development. The facility will be climate-controlled, making it an ideal destination year-round, especially during Florida’s hot summers and cooler winter months.

Tiki Tykes is more than just a play space — it is a community hub. We aim to become a trusted gathering place for local families by offering memberships, themed events, enrichment programs, and collaborative partnerships with local businesses and wellness professionals. With a focus on inclusivity, creativity, and connection, we are committed to meeting the evolving needs of our community through ongoing parent feedback and engagement.

 Our business model is built around recurring revenue through membership sales, drop-in passes, birthday parties, and retail offerings. With a strategic location in a rapidly growing family market and a concept that fills a current gap in the area, Tiki Tykes Island Play is positioned to become a cherished part of daily life for families on Amelia Island and beyond.

**Business Philosophy**

At Tiki Tykes Island Play, we believe that play is more than entertainment — it’s the foundation of growth, connection, and community. Our business is built on the understanding that families need safe, welcoming spaces where both children and parents can feel supported, engaged, and inspired.

We are guided by four core principles:

I. Connection First \- We view our space as a catalyst for building relationships between children and caregivers, among local families, and within the broader Amelia Island community. We intentionally create opportunities for meaningful social interaction, collaboration, and support.

II. Intentional Design \- Every element of our space, from the coastal-inspired play structures to the amenities offered to parents, is thoughtfully crafted to blend fun, safety, and beauty. We strive to maintain a high-end yet approachable environment that sparks imagination and joy.

III. Community-Centered Growth \- We see our customers as partners. Through regular feedback, focus groups, and real-time conversations, we evolve our offerings to reflect what families truly need and value. Our success is measured not just by revenue, but by the strength of the relationships we build.

IV. Local Loyalty \- We are committed to working with and supporting other local businesses. By sourcing locally and forming meaningful partnerships, we strengthen the community we serve — and ensure that our impact extends far beyond our walls.

Ultimately, our philosophy is simple: when families feel valued, supported, and inspired, communities thrive — and we’re here to help make that happen every day.

**Industry**

### **Perfect Fit for a Family-Centered Community \-** Amelia Island and the surrounding Fernandina Beach area are home to a growing population of young families seeking safe, enriching, and community-focused spaces for their children. With over **1,300 children under age 5** in the immediate 32034 ZIP code—and more than **4,200 in Nassau County**—there is a strong, underserved demand for high-quality play, learning, and wellness experiences for both children and parents.

#### **Filling a Market Gap \-** While the area features a few child-centric destinations, none offer the **premium, themed, boutique-style indoor play** experience Tiki Tykes will provide. Most competitors lack:

* Local identity and coastal theming

* Full-family support offerings (e.g. fitness, postpartum, sensory, and enrichment)  
* Thoughtful amenities for caregivers, like pop-up wellness services and a relaxing environment

By positioning Tiki Tykes as a **modern, lifestyle-forward space for young families**, it will  fill a highly desirable niche—creating not just a play space, but a trusted community hub.

#### **Strategic Growth Timing \-** Nassau County is one of the fastest-growing counties in Florida, with the population expected to exceed **109,000 by 2025** and up to **148,000 by 2035**. This includes many **young, upper-middle-income families** moving into new residential developments. Tiki Tykes is uniquely poised to grow with this population by:

* Establishing local brand loyalty early  
* Offering scalable membership models  
* Partnering with local businesses and professionals to expand services over time

**Deep Community Roots & Business Expertise \-**  Your strong local insight—paired with your **business degree, master’s in event management, and 10+ years of planning experience**—gives you a competitive edge. You know how to design experiences that keep families coming back, and you have the operational know-how to grow sustainably. Plus, your plan to partner with pediatricians, doulas, therapists, and other wellness providers deepens your local impact and adds value to every membership.

**Tiki Tykes will thrive** because it’s more than just a play place—it’s a vibrant, local-first destination where young families feel seen, supported, and inspired. You’re bringing something fresh, needed, and community-enhancing to a rapidly growing, family-rich island.

**Company Ownership/Legal Entity**

Tiki Tykes Island Play will operate as a Limited Liability Company (LLC) registered in the state of Florida. This structure offers the flexibility of a small business with the liability protection of a corporation, ensuring that the owner’s personal assets remain protected from any debts or legal actions related to the business.

The company is 100% owned and managed by Cayla and Jake Gutierrez, who will oversee all aspects of business operations, strategic planning, partnerships, and community engagement. As a single-member LLC, the business will benefit from simplified tax filing while maintaining full control and autonomy in decision-making.

This legal structure is ideal for the nature of the business, allowing for future scalability, potential investment opportunities, and the ability to hire employees or bring on partners as the company grows.

**Location**

Amelia Island, Florida. 

**Hours of Operation**

**Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday: 9:00 AM – 12:00 PM, 3:00 PM \- 5:00 PM**

* **Why:** These hours align with the routines of stay-at-home parents, caregivers, and part-time working parents. Young children are often most active in the morning, and many nap in the afternoon (1–3 PM).  
* **Optional:** Stay open until 5:00 PM a few days a week for after-school drop-ins, working parents, or special programming.

**Saturday: 9:00 AM – 1:00 PM**

* **Why:** Saturday mornings are a popular time for family outings. These hours also leave room for **birthday parties or private rentals** in the afternoon.  
* **Optional:** Extend to 3:00 PM if demand is high for weekend play.

**Sunday: Closed or Private Events Only**

* **Why:** Sundays are often slower for drop-in traffic but are great for **birthday parties or private group bookings**. You can maximize revenue with fewer staff on duty.

**Additional Ideas**

·        “Early Bird” Play Specials for guests arriving before 9AM  (encourages early traffic)        After-Hours Events once or twice a month: Parent mixers, sensory-friendly nights, or pajama play parties.

·        Member-Only Hours could be added in off-peak times to increase perceived value.
